# Chat vision attachments (IAM)

Implement image vision attachments **without** automatically storing every image.

## Default behavior (`ephemeral_vision`)

- Images attached to chat are **ephemeral** (describe/analyze/inspect only).
- Frontend shows a **local blob preview**; on send, include image files in the same `multipart/form-data` POST as the message.
- Use field name **`images`** for image files (non-image attachments use **`files`**).
- Set **`image_handling_mode=ephemeral_vision`** unless the user intent says otherwise.
- Backend reads uploaded bytes in `src/core/chat-composer-attachments.js`, builds vision blocks, forwards to a vision-capable model, then **discards** — no R2, D1, or project asset row.

## Three modes

| Mode | When | Storage |
|------|------|---------|
| `ephemeral_vision` | Default — "what do you see?", "analyze this screenshot" | None |
| `temporary_context` | Multi-turn reference ("keep this screenshot while debugging") | `SESSION_CACHE` TTL 1–24h via `chat-vision-temp-store.js` |
| `persisted_asset` | Explicit save ("save to project", "use as hero", "add to CMS") | Agent uses upload/asset tools — **not** auto on attach |

## Vision error codes (replace generic "could not read image")

- `NO_IMAGE_FILE_IN_REQUEST`
- `IMAGE_TOO_LARGE`
- `UNSUPPORTED_IMAGE_MIME`
- `MODEL_NOT_VISION_CAPABLE`
- `PROVIDER_REJECTED_IMAGE`
- `VISION_ADAPTER_FAILED`

## Key files

- `dashboard/components/ChatAssistant/ChatAssistant.tsx` — FormData: `images`, `image_handling_mode`
- `src/api/agent.js` — parse `files` + `images` from multipart
- `src/core/chat-composer-attachments.js` — parse, mode resolve, vision blocks
- `src/core/mode-controllers/agent-controller.js` — inject vision into user message, emit structured errors
